chat_history.message: My name is Muhammed Sajad PP, but you can call me Sajad.
I am a multifaceted professional with experience in backend development, video editing, photography, web design, SEO, and I am currently a machine learning student.
I have skills in programming languages such as JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, C, and C++.
I use tools like Premiere Pro and Photoshop in my work.
I am the founder of Grovix Lab, a startup focused on various tech solutions.
I developed a library management software called 'Katha,' which is published under the MIT license.
Currently, I am working on a library management system named Luminara for NHSS Kolathur.
I run a public Minecraft SMP server for free-to-play players.
I am also developing a bottle recycling product in India to tackle plastic waste.
I have a keen interest in machine learning and robotics, and I am aiming to learn the basics of machine learning to develop a GPT model.
I enjoy writing and am currently working on a story titled 'Sixth Myth,' which focuses on college friends and their adventures.
I have started a coding YouTube channel to share my knowledge and skills.
I am actively involved in community engagement, organizing workshops like 'Webix v1.0: From Web Designing to Web Development.'
Additionally, I participate in social initiatives, such as donation drives for disaster relief.
I am based in Kerala and am enthusiastic about digital marketing and branding, particularly through HAP Media.
I actively contribute to the Node.js community with npm packages.
